  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "YC6pNjf+z7iFKHWWVLeZQW+kA5U=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Build order: three milestones\n\n### Milestone 1 \u2014 MVP (polling, no GSOC)\n\nGoal: two users, one drive, invitation \u2192 accept \u2192 B's edit appears in A's toolbar History within ~5 s (existing poll interval). Proves the full loop on real Bee nodes.\n\nIncludes: types + manifest format, `CollabManager` (create/accept/list/leave), SwarmChannel peer-feed registration with per-source cursors, collab-scoped push path (second ACT upload), Chat UI Collaborate tab, `CollabInviteCard`, toolbar History auto-refresh.\n\n### Milestone 2 \u2014 GSOC real-time upgrade\n\n1. `GsocNotifier.onOpCommitted` \u2014 subscribe to each participant's signer.\n2. Send pings on push \u2014 `op-committed` GSOC message to each other participant after a collab-feed update.\n3. Debounced pull on ping \u2014 SwarmChannel pulls that writer's feed, coalescing bursts with ~300 ms debounce.\n4. Background signer mining \u2014 first collab create/accept kicks off mining without blocking the UI; polling is the fallback until mining completes.\n5. Latency smoke test: peer sees new revision in History within ~1\u20132 s of sender commit.\n\n### Milestone 3 \u2014 Document-level scope\n\n1. Narrow the ACT chain to the doc's feeds only (exclude drive manifest + sibling docs).\n2. Participant join gets just the one doc, not the containing drive.\n3. UI differentiates \"Shared document: X\" from drive-level collabs.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
    }
  },
